The Office of the Accountant General of the Federation (OAGF) is reviewing treasury forms and other accounting source documents used by Ministries, Department, and Agencies (MDAs). A statement by the spokesman, Mr. Henshaw Ogubike, said the Accountant General of the Federation, Ahmed Idris, has inaugurated an inter-ministerial committee on the review. Open treasury portal gets committee FG initiates 43 reforms in civil service in five years He noted that the contents of the treasury forms and other accounting source documents in use were no longer relevant and useful in driving the various public finance management reforms that are now ICT-driven. Ahmed said the committee was expected to identify all treasury forms and accounting source documents, initiate new formats, and recommend additions or deletions of contents, among others. He urged the committee to be guided by the federal government’s quest for adoption of e-governance at all levels. The Office of the Accountant General of the Federation (OAGF) is reviewing treasury forms and other accounting source documents used by Ministries, Department, and Agencies (MDAs). A statement by the spokesman, Mr. Henshaw Ogubike, said the Accountant General of the Federation, Ahmed Idris, has inaugurated an inter-ministerial committee on the review. Open treasury portal gets committee FG initiates 43 reforms in civil service in five years He noted that the contents of the treasury forms and other accounting source documents in use were no longer relevant and useful in driving the various public finance management reforms that are now ICT-driven. Ahmed said the committee was expected to identify all treasury forms and accounting source documents, initiate new formats, and recommend additions or deletions of contents, among others. He urged the committee to be guided by the federal government’s quest for adoption of e-governance at all levels.